---
import Layout from "../layouts/BlogPost.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="A little bit about michael-baker-content"
  pubDate={new Date("2025-01-01")}
>
  <p>
    Hi, I'm Michael. This blog is where I write in depth about projects I'm
    working on — the thinking behind them, what I learned, and what I'd do
    differently. It's a companion to my
    <a href="https://github.com/michael-baker-content">GitHub profile</a>, where
    the code lives.
  </p>

  <h2>What I work on</h2>

  <p>
    My interests span a pretty wide range. On the web development side I'm
    working through a structured frontend curriculum covering HTML, CSS,
    JavaScript, React, and Node.js. I enjoy building small tools and
    experimenting with APIs — my NBA Roto Tracker was an early experiment in
    that direction, built with Flask and deployed on Railway.
  </p>

  <p>
    I'm drawn to the intersection of code and creativity. I've been exploring
    generative art and creative coding with p5.js, and I'm curious about
    audio-reactive visuals using tools like Strudel. Math shows up in my work
    too — I've been learning LaTeX for typesetting equations and exploring data
    science with Python, NumPy, Matplotlib, and Seaborn.
  </p>

  <p>
    On the design side I use Figma regularly and have experimented with Webflow
    and Framer for design-to-deployment workflows. I'm also curious about
    self-hosted tools and have been thinking about standing up a WordPress
    instance from the terminal.
  </p>

  <h2>About this blog</h2>

  <p>
    Posts here tend to be project-driven rather than tutorial-style. I write
    about what I actually built, what problems I ran into, and what I found
    interesting along the way. If you want to follow along, the best place to
    start is the <a href="/blog">blog index</a> or browse by
    <a href="/tags">tag</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
